
<b>Click in tiles (java needed).</b>
(name : <tt>clicktile</tt>)
<br>

An applet (by Joke Evers) shows colored tiles. Some polygonal lines or (exclusif) one point
can be showed. Some tiles must be colored differently by the student by clicking on.

<p>Command <tt>\embed</tt> must be used. Each tile is given by the left-top corner
by something like <tt>integer:integer</tt>. 
The first line of the command <tt>\embed</tt> is the size X x Y  in pixels of the applet.
The second line inside  <tt>[</tt> <tt>]</tt> contains commands precising colored tiles
which will be presented (they can't be modified by the student) : for example,
<pre>
\embed{r1, 200 x 200
[xrange -5,5
yrange -5,5
background_color yellow
square blue,1:1,1:2,1:3
square green,2:3,2:4
point red,0:0]}
</pre>
The bounds (<tt>xrange</tt> et <tt>yrange</tt>) must be integers. 
The good answer is given by lines as
<tt>color,a:b,c:d</tt>
The tile points must be of the forme <tt>a:b</tt>
with <tt>a</tt> and <tt>b</tt>integers

For the background draw, one of the following lines is possible
<pre>
polygon white,0:0,0:1,1:1
point red,0:0
line white,-5:0,5:0
</pre>
It is possible to put an image in background. 
<pre>copy,x,y,url
</pre>
If done with flydraw, the url is the result of the function <tt>draw()</tt>. It is recommanded
to take the same <tt>xrange</tt> and <tt>yrange</tt>. 

The variable <tt>reply</tt>n is the matrix of selected tiles (one line by color).
If the line
<pre>
return_all_objects yes
</pre>
is in the second line of the command <tt>\embed</tt>, all tiles will be returned in <tt>reply</tt>n.
The variable <tt>sc_reply</tt>n is equal to 0.5 if all clicked tiles are correct but not of the asked color

<p>An empty variable can be put in the good reply. The analysis must be done with conditions in this
case.
</p>
<p>
<b>Example</b> : 
<pre>
\statement{
  \embed{r1,200 x 200
  [xrange -5,5
   yrange -5,5
   background_color yellow
   square blue,1:1,1:2,1:3
   square green,2:3,2:4
   line white,-5:0,5:0
  ]}
}
\answer{}{blue,1:0,1:-1,1:-2; green,2:-2,2:-3}{type=clicktile}
</pre>
